This problem can be solved using dynamic programming by building a 2D table where each cell represents whether a subset of the given numbers can sum up to a certain target.

```python
def subset_sum(xs, target):
    dp = [[False] * (target + 1) for _ in range(len(xs) + 1)]
    for i in range(len(xs) + 1):
        dp[i][0] = True
    for i in range(1, len(xs) + 1):
        for j in range(1, target + 1):
            dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j]
            if xs[i-1] <= j:
                dp[i][j] = dp[i][j] or dp[i-1][j-xs[i-1]]
    return dp[-1][-1]
```
